# buttons

Non-blocking button state-machine supporting:
- Single click
- Double click
- Triple click
- Hold (long press ≥ 700 ms)
- Simultaneous press of both buttons (click and hold)

Both buttons are configured with **internal pull-up**; the second contact
of each button is wired to **GND**.  A pressed button reads LOW.

## Hardware connection

| Button | ESP32-C3 GPIO |
| ------ | ------------- |
| Left   | GPIO 6        |
| Right  | GPIO 5        |

Both buttons: second contact → GND.

## API

```c
// Configure GPIOs and reset internal state.
void buttons_init(int gpio_l, int gpio_r);

// Poll button state.  Call every ~50 ms from the main loop.
// Returns a BTN_* event if one is ready, otherwise BTN_NONE.
btn_event_t buttons_poll(void);
```

## Event types (`btn_event_t`)

| Value            | Description                                 |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `BTN_NONE`       | No event ready                              |
| `BTN_L_CLICK`    | Single click — left button                  |
| `BTN_R_CLICK`    | Single click — right button                 |
| `BTN_L_DCLICK`   | Double click — left button                  |
| `BTN_R_DCLICK`   | Double click — right button                 |
| `BTN_L_TCLICK`   | Triple click — left button                  |
| `BTN_R_TCLICK`   | Triple click — right button                 |
| `BTN_L_HOLD`     | Hold (≥ 700 ms) — left button               |
| `BTN_R_HOLD`     | Hold (≥ 700 ms) — right button              |
| `BTN_BOTH_CLICK` | Both buttons released before hold threshold |
| `BTN_BOTH_HOLD`  | Both buttons held ≥ 700 ms                  |

## Timing constants (defined in buttons.c)

| Constant    | Value  | Meaning                                 |
| ----------- | ------ | --------------------------------------- |
| `HOLD_MS`   | 700 ms | Minimum press duration to register hold |
| `DCLICK_MS` | 350 ms | Max gap between clicks in a multi-click |
